  "text": "Psychology of working. The role of work in the lives of individuals is undoubtedly critical. People spend a significant amount of time working, whether it is actually the time spent at work, time preparing oneself for the workforce, or making plans for retirement. The importance of work is especially pronounced when examining those who do not work-how they suffer because of iteconomically, socially, and personally. For example, the research on the impact of unemployment on people's well-being has received a significant amount of empirical attention. One of the recent meta-analyses including 237 cross-sectional and 87 longitudinal studies [CITATION_1] revealed that there are clear mental health consequences of unemployment. The average overall effect size was d ¼ .51, indicating that the unemployed were significantly more distressed than the employed.",
